cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM. 

The paper proposes a novel framework for instance-level object segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a recursive and reversible approach to optimize the two sub-networks during joint training, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The proposed framework involves object proposal refinement, which is related to robotics and autonomous systems. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on the PASCAL VOC 2012 benchmark, which involves image and video processing. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category.
